# Architecture

## Repository layout

```
emby-player/
├── lib/                      # Flutter app
│   ├── main.dart             # MultiProvider boot
│   ├── providers/            # UI state (ChangeNotifier)
│   ├── services/             # IO, clients, platform, persistence helpers
│   ├── screens/              # Route-level UI
│   ├── widgets/              # Reusable UI (TV focus aware)
│   ├── domain/               # Abstract interfaces (MediaDataSource)
│   ├── data/                 # Adapters (EmbyMediaDataSource)
│   ├── connection/           # Connection model + registry
│   ├── profiles/             # Profile model + active profile
│   ├── media/                # Domain types (MediaItem, libraries)
│   ├── mpv/                  # Player abstraction + platform impls
│   ├── database/             # Drift AppDatabase
│   └── i18n/                 # slang JSON sources
├── packages/emby_core/       # Standalone Emby REST SDK
├── server/                   # Go watch-together relay
├── website/                  # SvelteKit marketing/docs site
└── scripts/                  # codegen, CI, release
```

## Layer rules (top → bottom)

| Layer | May depend on | Must not |
|-------|---------------|----------|
| **Widgets / Screens** | Providers, widgets, i18n | HTTP, Drift directly (prefer services) |
| **Providers** | Services, domain interfaces | Dio, raw SQL |
| **Services / Clients** | emby_core, database, platform | Widget `BuildContext` |
| **Domain** | media types only | Flutter, HTTP |
| **emby_core** | dio, models | Flutter, app services |

## Data flow (browse → play)

```
EmbyConnection (Drift)
  → ConnectionRegistry / MultiServerManager
  → EmbyClient (MediaServerClient)
  → EmbyMediaDataSource (MediaDataSource)
  → LibrariesProvider / screen
  → PlaybackInitializationResult
  → Player (MPV platform impl) via video_player screen
```

## Provider registration

- Register app-wide providers in `main.dart` `MultiProvider`.
- One canonical provider per domain (`LibrariesProvider`, `DownloadProvider`, …).
- Profile-scoped rebinding via `ActiveProfileBinder` — do not duplicate fetch logic in screens.

## Persistence

- **Drift** (`AppDatabase`) — connections, profiles, downloads, API cache, offline watch sync.
- **SharedPreferences** — settings via `SettingsService` / `BaseSharedPreferencesService`.
- Bump `schemaVersion` + implement migration for schema changes.

## Legacy Plezy surface

Large Plezy/Jellyfin/Plex code paths remain for gradual removal. **New work:**

- Target Emby API via `emby_core` or `EmbyClient`.
- Do not extend Jellyfin/Plex-specific mappers unless explicitly asked.
- `MediaBackend.fromString` defaults unknown IDs to emby with a warning.

## Cross-package changes

When changing Emby REST contracts:

1. Update `packages/emby_core` models/repositories first.
2. Adapt `lib/services/emby_client.dart` / mappers.
3. Update providers/screens last.

Run emby_core tests before app integration.
